{"type":"message","id":"7480ccc8","parentId":"a66c848d","timestamp":"2026-03-19T05:32:08.054Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting - the session_status shows 20% context usage, but the context-monitor.ps1 script reports 65%. This discrepancy might be due to the monitoring script using different metrics (totalTokens vs contextTokens).\n\nLooking at the script output:\n- Context usage: 65% (129695/200000 tokens)\n- This exceeds the 60% threshold\n\nAccording to the skill, when context reaches 60%, it should trigger automatic session switch. However, I also see from the session_status that this is actually just 20% - so there might be a discrepancy in how the monitor calculates context.\n\nActually, let me look more carefully. The session is \"agent:main:cron:696799cb-400f-4ac4-9393-6c861584965d\" which is this cron context monitor session. The 40k/200k is 20% which is fine.\n\nWait - I think I understand now. The context monitor is running as a cron job and checking the MAIN session (not this cron session). Let me verify by reading the script to see what it's actually monitoring.","thinkingSignature":"d362ecd281980a86b79bd9439b8957acd38ea758e9b24413faba967159a4ad3b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_sjdj6ii9fb7d_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Administrator\\.openclaw\\workspace\\skills\\miliger-context-manager\\scripts\\context-monitor.ps1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":3432,"output":276,"cacheRead":37002,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":40710,"cost":{"input":0.0010295999999999999,"output":0.0003312,"cacheRead":0.00111006,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00247086}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773898321325}}
{"type":"message","id":"df9d6896","parentId":"7480ccc8","timestamp":"2026-03-19T05:32:08.059Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_sjdj6ii9fb7d_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Context Monitor for Windows\n# Monitors OpenClaw session context usage and alerts when threshold is reached\n\nparam(\n    [int]$Threshold = 60,\n    [string]$LogDir = \"$env:USERPROFILE\\.openclaw\\workspace\\logs\",\n    [string]$LogFile = \"$LogDir\\context-monitor.log\"\n)\n\n# Ensure log directory exists\nif (!(Test-Path $LogDir)) {\n    New-Item -ItemType Directory -Path $LogDir -Force | Out-Null\n}\n\nfunction Write-Log($Message) {\n    $timestamp = Get-Date -Format \"yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss\"\n    \"$timestamp - $Message\" | Out-File -Append -FilePath $LogFile\n    Write-Host \"$timestamp - $Message\"\n}\n\n# Get session list to check context usage\ntry {\n    # Use .NET Process to properly separate stdout and stderr\n    $psi = New-Object System.Diagnostics.ProcessStartInfo\n    $psi.FileName = \"C:\\Users\\Administrator\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\openclaw.cmd\"\n    $psi.Arguments = \"sessions --json\"\n    $psi.RedirectStandardOutput = $true\n    $psi.RedirectStandardError = $true\n    $psi.UseShellExecute = $false\n    $psi.CreateNoWindow = $true\n    \n    $process = New-Object System.Diagnostics.Process\n    $process.StartInfo = $psi\n    $process.Start() | Out-Null\n    \n    $stdout = $process.StandardOutput.ReadToEnd()\n    $stderr = $process.StandardError.ReadToEnd()\n    $process.WaitForExit()\n    \n    if ($stdout) {\n        # Extract JSON from stdout (find content between first { and last })\n        $jsonStart = $stdout.IndexOf('{')\n        $jsonEnd = $stdout.LastIndexOf('}')\n        \n        if ($jsonStart -ge 0 -and $jsonEnd -gt $jsonStart) {\n            $jsonContent = $stdout.Substring($jsonStart, $jsonEnd - $jsonStart + 1)\n            $data = $jsonContent | ConvertFrom-Json -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue\n            \n            if ($data -and $data.sessions) {\n                # Find main session\n                $mainSession = $data.sessions | Where-Object { $_.key -eq 'agent:main:main' } | Select-Object -First 1\n                \n                if ($mainSession -and $mainSession.totalTokens -and $mainSession.contextTokens) {\n                    $used = $mainSession.totalTokens\n                    $total = $mainSession.contextTokens\n                    $usage = [math]::Round(($used / $total) * 100)\n                    \n                    Write-Log \"Context usage: ${usage}% (${used}/${total} tokens)\"\n                    \n                    if ($usage -ge $Threshold) {\n                        Write-Log \"WARNING: Context usage ${usage}% exceeds threshold ${Threshold}%\"\n                        \n                        # Check memory files\n                        $memoryDir = \"$env:USERPROFILE\\.openclaw\\workspace\\memory\"\n                        $memoryLite = \"$memoryDir\\MEMORY-LITE.md\"\n                        \n                        if (Test-Path $memoryLite) {\n                            $content = Get-Content $memoryLite -Raw -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue\n                            $wordCount = ($content -split '\\s+').Count\n                            Write-Log \"MEMORY-LITE.md: $wordCount words\"\n                        }\n                        \n                        Write-Log \"ALERT: Consider starting a new session to reset context\"\n                    } else {\n                        Write-Log \"Context usage normal: ${usage}%\"\n                    }\n                } else {\n                    Write-Log \"Main session found but no token info available\"\n                }\n            } else {\n                Write-Log \"No sessions data found in JSON\"\n            }\n        } else {\n            Write-Log \"Could not find JSON content in output\"\n        }\n    } else {\n        Write-Log \"No output from sessions command\"\n    }\n} catch {\n    Write-Log \"Error checking context: $_\"\n}\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773898328057}}
{"type":"message","id":"dfa9c062","parentId":"df9d6896","timestamp":"2026-03-19T05:32:13.147Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see - the script is checking the main session (`agent:main:main`). The output shows 65% usage (129695/200000 tokens). This is monitoring the main session's context.\n\nBut the session_status I just checked shows only 20% for the current session (which is the cron session, not the main session).\n\nThe script is designed to monitor the main session and alert when it reaches threshold. It found 65% usage which exceeds 60% threshold. According to the skill:\n- At 60% threshold, it should trigger automatic session switch\n- But this script only logs an alert - it doesn't actually trigger the switch\n\nLet me check the main session's status directly to confirm the context usage.","thinkingSignature":"a5111c11193c0c9b4b156d4a6a0a0a8d40a9d225bcffe0ec68c40d9731f8a4f8"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_nutsua0pc4ia_1","name":"session_status","arguments":{"sessionKey":"agent:main:main"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":4557,"output":176,"cacheRead":37002,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":41735,"cost":{"input":0.0013671,"output":0.00021119999999999998,"cacheRead":0.00111006,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00268836}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773898328059}}
