{"type":"message","id":"a053ea45","parentId":"8884cc2e","timestamp":"2026-03-19T05:32:22.238Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Confirmed! The main session (`agent:main:main`) is at 65% context usage (130k/200k), which exceeds the 60% threshold. This means we need to trigger a seamless session switch.\n\nAccording to the context manager skill:\n- When context reaches 60%, trigger automatic session switch\n- Save memory to MEMORY.md\n- Update MEMORY-LITE.md\n- Update daily log\n- Trigger agentTurn to create new session\n\nHowever, looking at the current implementation, the context-monitor.ps1 script only logs an alert - it doesn't actually perform the switch. I need to either:\n1. Manually trigger the switch\n2. Or check if there's another mechanism\n\nActually, wait - looking more carefully at the skill, it seems like this should be automated via cron jobs using the agentTurn mechanism. Let me check if there's a separate cron job for the actual session switch, or if I need to manually trigger this.\n\nGiven the skill mentions:\n- \"无感自动切换\" - seamless automatic switch\n- \"自动触发：上下文达到60%自动切换\"\n- The script should trigger agentTurn\n\nBut the current script only logs. Let me check if there's supposed to be another component that does the actual switch.\n\nActually, I should follow the skill's guidance. The monitor has detected 65% which exceeds 60%. I need to:\n1. Save the current session memory\n2. Create a new session via agentTurn\n\nLet me check the current memory files and then proceed with the switch process.","thinkingSignature":"8dc4abe2b07eae41ffcc9f3c253a22d72adbf6f1f682fd4ac256e260ab2ccb15"},{"type":"text","text":"The main session is at **65% context usage** (130k/200k), exceeding the 60% threshold. I'll proceed with the automatic session switch as designed.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_uax3wqu9uuiu_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Administrator\\.openclaw\\workspace\\MEMORY.md"}}],"